    "content": "Apologies for not explicitly acknowledging your earlier feedback, Carson. Confirming: yes, the implementation uses the existing `POST /inbox/{id}/clarify` endpoint with `clarify_type=waiting_for` as a form field value -- exactly as you advocated. No separate endpoint was created.\n\nThe route handler in `src/routes/inbox.rs` checks `form.clarify_type == \"waiting_for\"` as the first branch (before \"project\" and the default \"next_action\"), so the form action stays the same regardless of which radio is selected. Progressive enhancement works cleanly -- no JS needed to switch endpoints.\n\nHTMX attributes on the clarify form remain unchanged:\n- `hx-post=\"/inbox/{{ item.id }}/clarify\"`\n- `hx-target=\"#inbox-item-{{ item.id }}\"`\n- `hx-swap=\"outerHTML\"`\n\nOn success, returns empty body with `HX-Trigger: {\"announce\":\"Moved to Waiting For\"}` -- item disappears from the list.\n\nImplementation is complete with all tests passing. Ready for your review of the HTMX interactions if you'd like to examine the code."
  }
}
